description.displayText:
Jess is amazing. She was our full-time nanny/house manager for about 18 months, and during that time, she demonstrated an exceptional level of professionalism, kindness, and dedication to the care of our children. She quickly became a beloved member of our family, and we cannot recommend her highly enough. Jess was an incredibly responsible caregiver, always making sure that our children were safe, happy, and well-cared-for. She was punctual, reliable, and dependable, and we never had to worry about the girls' well-being when they were in her care.  She has an incredible gift for connecting with children, and our girls adored her. 

Jess was responsible for school pickups, meal prep, helping with projects, children's laundry, and entertaining the girls. Additionally, she handled house manager duties such as meal planning, grocery shopping, getting quotes and coordinating home projects, and anything else we needed. Overall, we cannot recommend Jess highly enough.

description.displayText: Jessica has been our full time many since August 2016. She loves our infant son like her own! She is dedicated, professional, responsible, playful, interactive, attentive and affectionate. She goes out of her way to find learning opportunities, social events, craft ideas, and physical activities for our little one. She is amazing and highly recommended by our family!

description.displayText: Jessica has been great for our family!  My 3 year-old daughter would cry and cling to us when we left for date-nights, but she really likes Jessica and now will just hug us and say bye!  They do special project together like painting, baking, and play-dough - our daughter actually looks forward to Jessica coming over!  We like that Jessica is an adult and has lots of childcare experience - we know our daughter will be well-cared for and that should an emergency arise, Jessica will be able to handle it calmly.  She also enforces our parenting philosophies so we know our daughter is getting consistent boundaries and care even if we are not there.

description.displayText:
It is my great pleasure to recommend Jessica as a nanny. She has been caring for our 4-year-old daughter and 11 month old daughter since August 2015.

Jessica is bright, reliable, and affectionate. She is also well-versed in child development, both due to her university studies and a natural affinity toward children. She relates to our daughter in such a delightful way. Jessica knows how to structure time well, but is also flexible. She is as comfortable helping our daughter through a preschool workbook as she is washing our cloth diapers and keeping things going around the house.
We feel fortunate to have had Jessica in our home as our full time nanny. We are convinced that our daughters owe much of their positive development to her presence. Her approach to caring for our daughters complements our parenting well, as she respects our personal philosophies while being confident enough to independently make day-to-day decisions regarding our daughter.

Please don't hesitate to contact me if you would like to hear more about our experiences with Jessica.

description.displayText: Jessica started nannying for my 15 month-old twin boys part-time in November 2014.  She cleaned bottles, made formula, washed baby laundry, prepared and fed meals, diapered, and played with my boys, and allowed me to run errands, go to the doctor, etc.  It did not take long for her to win them over.  She has a wonderful sense of fun and creative play with toddlers, and has the energy to handle my 2 feisty boys.  She also enjoyed taking them outside where they had lots of fun with her.  She helped me take them for swim lessons, and was a great support for one of my boys during this "new" experience.  We always feel confident leaving our boys with her.  She is able to multi-task which is an important skill with twins, and is dedicated and professional.  She is an excellent caregiver!
